h3cVoiceDialControl.name: h3cVoiceDialControl

h3cVoiceDialControl.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice dial control configuration.

h3cVoPeerCommonConfigTable.name: h3cVoPeerCommonConfigTable
h3cVoPeerCommonConfigTable.description: This table contains the general voice peer information.

h3cVoPeerCfgIndex.name: h3cVoPeerCfgIndex
h3cVoPeerCfgIndex.description: The index of a dial entity common table.

h3cVoPeerCfgRowStatus.name: h3cVoPeerCfgRowStatus
h3cVoPeerCfgRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table.

h3cVoPeerCfgDesPattern.name: h3cVoPeerCfgDesPattern
h3cVoPeerCfgDesPattern.description: This object indicates the caller number of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCodec1st.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCodec1st
h3cVoPeerCfgCodec1st.description: This object indicates the first desirable CODEC of speech of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCodec2nd.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCodec2nd
h3cVoPeerCfgCodec2nd.description: This object indicates the second desirable CODEC of speech of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCodec3rd.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCodec3rd
h3cVoPeerCfgCodec3rd.description: This object indicates the third desirable CODEC of speech of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCodec4th.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCodec4th
h3cVoPeerCfgCodec4th.description: This object indicates the forth desirable CODEC of speech of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgDSCP.name: h3cVoPeerCfgDSCP
h3cVoPeerCfgDSCP.description: This object indicates the DSCP(Different Service Code Point) value of voice packets.

h3cVoPeerCfgShutDown.name: h3cVoPeerCfgShutDown
h3cVoPeerCfgShutDown.description: This object indicates the current status of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgVADEnable.name: h3cVoPeerCfgVADEnable
h3cVoPeerCfgVADEnable.description: This object indicates whether the VAD(Voice Activity Detection) is enabled.

h3cVoPeerCfgOutbandMode.name: h3cVoPeerCfgOutbandMode
h3cVoPeerCfgOutbandMode.description: This object indicates the DTMF(Dual Tone Multi-Frequency) outband type of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLevel.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLevel
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLevel.description: This object indicates the fax level of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxBaudrate.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxBaudrate
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxBaudrate.description: This object indicates the fax baudrate of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLocalTrainPara.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLocalTrainPara
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxLocalTrainPara.description: This object indicates the fax local train threshold of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxProtocol.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxProtocol
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxProtocol.description: This object indicates the fax protocol of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxHRPackNum.name: h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxHRPackNum
h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxHRPackNum.description: This object indicates the high speed redundancy packet numbers.

h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxLRPackNum.name: h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxLRPackNum
h3cVoPeerCfgT38FaxLRPackNum.description: This object indicates the low speed redundancy packet numbers.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSendNSFEnable.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSendNSFEnable
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSendNSFEnable.description: This object indicates whether sends NSF(non-standard faculty) to fax of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSupportMode.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSupportMode
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxSupportMode.description: This object indicates the fax support mode of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxTrainMode.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxTrainMode
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxTrainMode.description: This object indicates the fax train mode of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgFaxEcm.name: h3cVoPeerCfgFaxEcm
h3cVoPeerCfgFaxEcm.description: This object indicates whether the ECM(error correct mode) is enabled.

h3cVoPeerCfgPriority.name: h3cVoPeerCfgPriority
h3cVoPeerCfgPriority.description: This object indicates the priority of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgDescription.name: h3cVoPeerCfgDescription
h3cVoPeerCfgDescription.description: This object indicates the textual description of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberType.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberType
h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberType.description: This object indicates the type of calling number of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberType.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberType
h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberType.description: This object indicates the type of called number of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberPlan.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberPlan
h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumberPlan.description: This object indicates the numbering plan of calling number of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberPlan.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberPlan
h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumberPlan.description: This object indicates the numbering plan of called number of this dial peer.

h3cVoPeerCfgSelectStop.name: h3cVoPeerCfgSelectStop
h3cVoPeerCfgSelectStop.description: This object indicates whether permitting the system to allocate alternative entities to establish a phone call.

h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumSubstRule.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumSubstRule
h3cVoPeerCfgCallingNumSubstRule.description: This object indicates number-substitute rule of calling number.

h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumSubstRule.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumSubstRule
h3cVoPeerCfgCalledNumSubstRule.description: This object indicates number-substitute rule of called number.

h3cVoPeerCfgMaxCall.name: h3cVoPeerCfgMaxCall
h3cVoPeerCfgMaxCall.description: The object indicates that this dial peer is bound with a tag that indicates a maximum call value.

h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigTable.name: h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigTable
h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigTable.description: This table contains the POTS(Public Switched Telephone Network) peer information.

h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex.name: h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex
h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex.description: The index of voice pots peer table.

h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix.name: h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix
h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix.description: This object indicates the prefix which is added to the called number.

h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSubLine.name: h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSubLine
h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSubLine.description: This object indicates the voice subscriber line of this dial peer.

h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNum.name: h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNum
h3cVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNum.description: This object indicates the digit of phone number to be sent to the destination.

h3cVoVoIPPeerConfigTable.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerConfigTable
h3cVoVoIPPeerConfigTable.description: This table contains the voip peer information.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgIndex.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgIndex
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgIndex.description: The index of voice voip peer table.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetType.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetType
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetType.description: This object indicates the type of the session target of this peer.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetAddrType.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetAddrType
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetAddrType.description: The IP address type of object h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetAddr.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetAddr.description: This object indicates the target ip address. This object is valid when h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTargetType is h323Ipv4 or sipIpv4.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgFastStart.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgFastStart
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgFastStart.description: This object indicates whether the fast connection function is enabled.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTunnel.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTunnel
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgTunnel.description: This object indicates whether the tunnel function is enabled.

h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgSendRing.name: h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgSendRing
h3cVoVoIPPeerCfgSendRing.description: This object indicates whether sending ring is enabled.

h3cVoPeerDefault1stCodecLevel.name: h3cVoPeerDefault1stCodecLevel
h3cVoPeerDefault1stCodecLevel.description: The default priority of the first level CODEC(coding and decoding).

h3cVoPeerDefault2ndCodecLevel.name: h3cVoPeerDefault2ndCodecLevel
h3cVoPeerDefault2ndCodecLevel.description: The default priority of the second level CODEC(coding and decoding).

h3cVoPeerDefault3rdCodecLevel.name: h3cVoPeerDefault3rdCodecLevel
h3cVoPeerDefault3rdCodecLevel.description: The default priority of the third level CODEC(coding and decoding).

h3cVoPeerDefault4thCodecLevel.name: h3cVoPeerDefault4thCodecLevel
h3cVoPeerDefault4thCodecLevel.description: The default priority of the fourth level CODEC(coding and decoding).

h3cVoPeerDefaultVADOn.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultVADOn
h3cVoPeerDefaultVADOn.description: The default value of dial peer's VAD(Voice Activity Detection).

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTransLevel.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTransLevel
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTransLevel.description: The default value of dial peer's fax transmit level. The unit is db.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLocalTrain.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLocalTrain
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLocalTrain.description: The default value of dial peer's fax local train threshold.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxProtocol.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxProtocol
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxProtocol.description: The default value of dial peer's fax protocol.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxHSRedunNum.description: The default value of dial peer's T38 fax protocol high redundancy packet number.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLSRedunNum.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLSRedunNum
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxLSRedunNum.description: The default value of dial peer's T38 fax protocol low redundancy packet number.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxBaudrate.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxBaudrate
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxBaudrate.description: The default value of dial peer's fax baudrate.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxNSF.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxNSF
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxNSF.description: The default value of fax NSF(non-standard faculty).

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxSupportMode.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxSupportMode
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxSupportMode.description: The default mode of fax supported.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTrainMode.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTrainMode
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxTrainMode.description: The default value of fax training mode.

h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxECM.name: h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxECM
h3cVoPeerDefaultFaxECM.description: The default value of fax ECM(Error Correct Mode) Mode.

h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitTable.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitTable
h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitTable.description: The table contains permitted caller number in the specific voice entity for incoming call.

h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitNum.name: h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitNum
h3cVoPeerCfgCallerPermitNum.description: This object specifies permitted caller number.

h3cVoPeerCallerPermitRowStatus.name: h3cVoPeerCallerPermitRowStatus
h3cVoPeerCallerPermitRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table.
